row.entry:
Magic angle spinning (MAS) sometimes with high-power decoupling (HPDEC) to reduce line broadening and anisotropic;
6Li NMR for better resolution;
Cross polarization (CP) to explore the spatial adjacent

Spin-spin relaxation time (T 2) and spin-lattice relaxation in rotation of frame of reference (T 1ρ) to motions at intermediate regime;
Spin-lattice relaxation in laboratory frame of reference (T 1) to measure rapid motions;
Pulsed field gradient (PFG) NMR to analyze long-range ion transport or spin diffusion;
2D-EXSY for slow two-site chemical exchange

Selective isotope labeling method (7Li- 6Li);
Rotation-echo double resonance (REDOR) etc. to quantity spatial adjacent;
2D heteronuclear correlation (HETCOR) NMR spectroscopy to establish correlations and nonactivities
